title: What font is "October" in?
content:
Hello! Just looking for what font October is in! Thank you!

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552im_/http:/typophile.com/files/IMG_5380_5071.jpg)
author: missblaser

comments.content:
I don't know what typeface that is but some fonts with a similar feel:  
 [Brownstone](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552/http:/www.sudtipos.com/fonts/133)  
 [Estilo Script](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/dstype/estilo-script/)  
 [Fox TRF](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/tipografiaramis/fox-trf/)  
 [Monroe](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/sudtipos/monroe/)

You can check out a few more on a previous post, [Structural sans-serif with swash?](http://web.archive.org/web/20150419064552/http:/typophile.com/node/69691)
